\f2\b\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 What is ISO 14971?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 ISO 14971 is the international standard which specifies requirements of risk management systems for medical devices. It explains the best practices considering the entire lifecycle of medical devices.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 What is the latest version of ISO 14971?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The latest version of ISO 14971 is specified as ISO 14971:2019 since it was released in 2019. Prior to this publication there were two earlier versions of ISO 14971 specified as ISO 14971:2007 and ISO 14971:2000. Also the European version of the same standard is referred as EN ISO 14971.\'a0\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Does US FDA recognizes the new version of ISO 14971?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) recognizes the new version of ISO 14971 along-with many other regulatory bodies throughout the world.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
