\fs60 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 The Reason to Update ISO 14971\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Medical devices need to be managed regarding the risks they can pose. Therefore, proper risk management is necessary to be carried out during the entire life cycle of a medical device. The International Organization for Standardization has devised the standard ISO 14971 to help the companies carry out the proper risk management process for their products. Recently, few changes were brought out into ISO 14971, and its Technical Report, ISO TR 2497, and the updated version of both were released as ISO 14971:2019 and ISO/TR24971:2020, respectively.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The updated version comes up with revisions in interpretations of the primary risk management process. In addition to this, the updated version also contains a discussion on Risk Management System alongside with risk management process.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 What were the Reasons to Update ISO 14971?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The reasons to update ISO 14971 are:
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Difficulty in Navigation\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 1610781389202927789.png \width2715 \height2685 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The previous versions of ISO 14971 were hard to navigate. They also contain inefficient information regarding the safety of medical devices.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Lack of Guidance in Risk Management\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16107813881618070977.png.webp \width3440 \height3540 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Earlier versions of ISO 14971 failed to guide the medical device manufacturers regarding risk management, hence were unable to complete the standard criteria.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Use of Outdated Definitions\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec9 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16107813891668108045.png.webp \width3200 \height3680 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The predecessors of ISO 14971 contained old definitions that do not fulfill risk management requirements for the modern medical device industry.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Correspondence with Other Standards\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Apart from the reasons listed above, one of the main reasons to update ISO 14971 was to align it with the requirements of EU MDR, EU IVDR, and ISO 13485:2016\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 To address the shortcomings present in the previous editions of ISO 14971, the International Standard for Standardization (ISO) and International Electrotechnical Commission (IEC) came together in 2016 to plan changes in the existing standard; the new standard was released on December 18, 2019. These updates also put their emphasis on the post-market FDA situation\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Both ISO and IEC also contributed to updating the technical report, i.e., ISO TR 24971. This technical report provides medical manufacturers with helpful guidance information.\cb1 \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 \
