\fs60 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Major Revisions in ISO 14971:2019\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The significant revisions made in ISO 14971:2019 as compared to its predecessors are as follows:\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Clause on Normative References\cb1 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16106295071563138375.png.webp \width3740 \height3800 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 To comply with the requirements for standardization; Clause 15 of ISO/IEC Directives, Part 2:2018, a clause on normative references has been included in the third edition. But there are no references here.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Defined Terms\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec9 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 1610629508470373837.png.webp \width3460 \height3440 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Defined terms are updated and printed in italic so that readers can identify them in the body of the document. In addition, many defined terms are derived from ISO/IEC Guide 63:2019.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Introduction of New Terms\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec9 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16106295081022934206.png \width3000 \height3405 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The terms benefit, reasonably foreseeable misuse, and state-of-the-art has been introduced and described in the third edition.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Benefit-Risk Analysis\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec9 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16106295091728677261.png \width2985 \height2880 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The third edition of ISO 14971 focuses on the benefits that the use of medical devices can offer. Also, the term Benefit-Risk Analysis has been aligned with the terminology used in other regulations.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Usage of Process
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16106304921230659337.png.webp \width5300 \height5420 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The term Process, described in the third edition of ISO 14971, can be used to manage risks associated with medical devices and those related to data and systems security.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Risk Management Plan
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16106309151204169697.png \width2655 \height3195 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 A risk management plan describes the method used to determine the overall residual risk and its acceptability criteria. The process can include collecting and evaluating data and other literature for the medical device and similar medical devices and other available products in the market. As a result, acceptability criteria for the overall residual risk can differ from the acceptability criteria of individual risks.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Requirements to Disclose Residual Risks
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16106304931274228683.png.webp \width5180 \height3180 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 After evaluating overall residual risk and its acceptance, the requirements to disclose residual risks have been shifted and merged into one condition.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Risk Management Report
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 1610781106654482637.png \width2250 \height2700 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The Risk Management Plan demands a review of the medical device before its commercial distribution. The results of this review ought to be documented in the risk management report.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Production & Post-Production Requirements
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 1610781009117563074.png \width2940 \height2985 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The third edition contains restructured requirements regarding production and post-production activities. In addition, detailed information is given regarding the collection of the information. The clause also lists the actions taken after reviewing the collected data and determining its relevance to safety.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Information Annexes
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16107810092020378928.png \width3450 \height1875 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 In the third edition of ISO 14971, more information and rationale for the requirements have been given in Annex A. The information covering correspondence between the clauses of the second edition with the third is provided in Annex B.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Major Updates in ISO 14971\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Risk Management Plan\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 16107826771285437803.png \width4005 \height2550 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 The revised version contains the Risk Management Plan. The standard also shows variations at different steps while describing the risk management plan. A medical device manufacturer may need to revise his process drawings accordingly with the standard in this regard.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Risk Analysis (Clause-5.4)
\fs28 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 {{\NeXTGraphic 1610782677353145234.png.webp \width5900 \height5320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Clause 5.4 on Risk Analysis has been made more precise and specific. The revised passage says:\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 \'93The manufacturer shall identify and the document known and foreseeable hazards associated with the medical device based on the intended use, reasonably foreseeable misuse and the characteristics related to safety in both normal and fault conditions.\'94
\f1\i0 \cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Now the approach on risk analysis won't be limited to fault condition analysis only. Rather, due to the addition of the paragraph above, there will be other factors to consider within the risk management process.\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

