\f0\fs26\fsmilli13125 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Accompanying Documentation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Accompanying Documentation is defined in Clause 3.1 as\'a0
\f4\i \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 '
\f5\b \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 materials accompanying a medical device and containing information for the user or those accountable for the installation, use, maintenance, decommissioning and disposal of the medical device, particularly regarding safe use.\'92
\f1\i0\b0 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Some important notes are:\'a0\
\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 \'95\'a0The accompanying documentation can consist of the instructions for use, technical description, installation manual, quick reference guide, etc.\'a0\
\'95\'a0Accompanying documentation is not necessarily a written or printed document but could involve auditory, visual, or tactile materials and multiple media types.\
\

\f0\fs22\fsmilli11250 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Intended Use or Purpose\
