\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 \'95\'a0control of conception\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 \'95\'a0disinfection of medical devices\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 \'95\'a0providing information by means of in vitro examination of specimens derived from the human body, and which does not achieve its primary intended action by pharmacological, immunological or metabolic means, in or on the human body, but which may be assisted in its function by such means.'\cf5 \cb1 \strokec5 \
