\f2\b\fs36 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Lesson Summary\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The complete name of ISO 14971:2019 is ISO 14971:2019 Medical Devices-Application of Risk Management to Medical Devices.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The requirements of ISO 14971:2019 are applicable on phases of the life cycle of a medical device such that the risks associated with medical devices, their biocompatibility, data, and systems security, electricity, moving parts, radiation, and usability are addressed thoroughly.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The requirements of ISO 14971:2019 exempt the following from its scope:
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\b \cb3 \'95
\f1\b0 \'a0Decisions regarding the use of a medical device in the context of any specific clinical procedure;\cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\b \cb3 \'95
\f1\b0 \'a0Business risk management.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The third edition of ISO 14971 focuses on the benefits of the use of medical devices. Also, the term Benefit-Risk Analysis has been aligned with the terminology used in other regulations.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Usage of Process
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The term Process, described in the third edition of ISO 14971, can be used to manage risks associated with medical devices and those related to data and systems security.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls16\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Risk Management Plan
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 A risk management plan describes the method to determine the overall residual risk and its acceptability criteria.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls17\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Requirements to Disclose Residual Risks
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 After evaluating overall residual risk and its acceptance, the requirements to disclose residual risks have been shifted and merged into one single requirement.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls18\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Risk Management Report
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The Risk Management Plan demands a review of the medical device before its commercial distribution. The results of this review ought to be documented in the risk management report.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls19\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Production & Post-Production Requirements
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The third edition contains restructured requirements regarding production and post-production activities. In addition, detailed information is given regarding the collection of the information. The clause also lists the actions to be taken after reviewing the collected data and determining its relevance to safety.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls20\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Information Annexes
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 In the third edition of ISO 14971, more information and rationale for the requirements have been given in Annex A. The data covering correspondence between the clauses of the second edition with the third is provided in Annex B.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls21\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The Reason to Update ISO 14971\cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 \cb3 Medical devices need to be managed regarding the risks they can pose. Therefore, proper risk management is necessary to be carried out during the entire life cycle of a medical device. The International Organization for Standardization has devised the standard ISO 14971 to help the companies carry out the proper risk management process for their products.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls22\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The previous versions of ISO 14971 were hard to navigate. They also contain inefficient information regarding the safety of medical devices.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls23\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Earlier versions of ISO 14971 failed to guide the medical device manufacturers regarding risk management, hence were unable to complete the standard criteria.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls24\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The predecessors of ISO 14971 contained old definitions that do not fulfill risk management requirements for the modern medical device industry.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls25\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Correspondence with Other Standards
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 To address the shortcomings present in the previous editions of ISO 14971, the International Standard for Standardization (ISO) and International Electrotechnical Commission (IEC) came together in 2016 to plan changes in the existing standard; the new standard was released on December 18, 2019. These updates also put their emphasis on the post-market FDA situation.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls26\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Overview of Changes Made in ISO 14971
