\f2\b\fs32 \cf5 \cb3 Details of Changes Made in ISO 14971
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls28\ilvl0
\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Clause 2 of ISO 14971:2019 is entirely new. It deals with Normative References, which is the requirement of the ISO Technical Management Board. ISO 14971\'92s clause 2 states that there are \'93no normative references.\'94\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls29\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 In the 2019 version of ISO 14971, clauses have been renumbered and incremented by 1 from this clause on wards.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 Lesson Summary\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls30\ilvl0
\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Addition of New Terms & Definitions
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Benefit (Clause-3.2)\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Harm (Clause-3.3)\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Reasonably Foreseeable Misuse (Clause-3.15)\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 State of the Art (Clause-3.28)\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls31\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Risk Management Plan
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The revised version contains the Risk Management Plan in Figure 1 of clause 4.1. The standard also shows variations at different steps while describing the risk management plan. A medical device manufacturer may need to revise his process drawings accordingly with the standard in this regard.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls32\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Risk Analysis (Clause-5.4)
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls33\ilvl0\cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Clause 5.4 on Risk Analysis has been made more precise and specific. The revised passage says:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls34\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'93The manufacturer shall identify and document the known and foreseeable hazards associated with the medical device based on the intended use, reasonably foreseeable misuse and the characteristics related to safety in both normal and fault conditions.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls35\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Because many tools are only fault condition analysis, this section now requires the use of multiple risk analysis tools.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls36\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Benefit-Risk Analysis (Clause-7.4)
\f1\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Clause 7.4 has been renamed Benefit-Risk Analysis. The risks declared as unacceptable; the standard requires only those risks to have a Benefit-Risk Analysis.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls37\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf5 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Production & Post-Production Activities (Clause-10)\cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 \cb3 Instead of waiting for complaints, clause 10 now focuses on having an active process for collecting information, and it also requires risk management in post-market surveillance.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

